[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[size=3]Crafting drops red / green / blue XP points as physical orbs that fly around until you walk near them. A big uncollected pile of these is a massive performance drain. This mod adds the points directly to your XP bar instead of spawning an orb at all, so there's nothing to collect and nothing to slow the game down.[/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][b]No more orb sinks[/b] — XP points from any craft, action, or quest go straight into your XP totals. Existing orbs lying around your map still work like normal (walk over them); only new points are inlined.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]HUD feedback[/b] — a short text pop above the keeper's head (same style as energy-spend text) shows the number and colour of points just added. Toggle off if you want a clean HUD.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]No gating[/b] — applies as soon as the mod loads, to every XP-awarding action in the game.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Other mods of mine you might like[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/70]Give Me Moar[/url] — multipliers on red/green/blue tech points (and much more).[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/51]Auto-Loot Heavies[/url] — removes the other big mid-late-game clutter problem (stockpiles of timber, stone, marble, ore).[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/57]Queue Everything[/url] — auto-craft whole batches. Combines with Where's Ma' Points to turn idle crafting into passive XP with zero performance hit.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/55]Misc. Bits and Bobs[/url] — includes "Condense XP Bar" to shorten big XP numbers on the HUD.[/size]
[/list]
[size=4][b]Configuration[/b][/size]

[size=3]If you installed the required [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack[/url] and this mod is configurable, press F1 in-game to open the config interface.[/size]

[size=4][b]Requirements[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79][size=3]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack at Graveyard Keeper Nexus - Mods and community (nexusmods.com)[/size][/url]
[/list]
[size=4][b]Installation[/b][/size]

[size=3]Installation using Vortex is the recommended installation method. If you wish to install manually, extract the contents of the mod archive into:

[code]...&#92;steamapps&#92;common&#92;Graveyard Keeper&#92;BepInEx[/code][/size]

